baconBits

This module is used to automate uploads to baconBits.  
If you don't know what that is, you're probably in the wrong place.

INSTALLATION

This module requires you have installed pythonbits and ctorrent

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc baconBits


SYNTAX
Currently, source, episode, and series are all required

bbupload.pl --source=<path_to_dir> --episode=<SXXEXX> --series=<name>
bbupload.pl -s <path_to_dir> -e <SXXEXX> -r <name>

bbupload.pl --source=/media/stor/Video/Archer.2009.S03E04.HDTV.XviD-ASAP --episode=S03E04 --series=Archer

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=baconBits

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
